This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.

Learn More

TECH CLUB

“Fiestron – Our Tech Territory” is an initiative taken by the students of the Department of Computer Science of K.C. College for their Annual Festival. Fies-Tron is an Inter collegiate fest of 2 days in which a lot of colleges participate across Mumbai. The aim of this festival is to introduce students to the recent developments in the field of Computer Science in an exciting and interesting manner. Last year we had renowned personalities like: Mr. Keki Mistry, Vice Chairman and CEO of HDFC Robin Catchpole, astronomer at the Institute of Astronomy, Cambridge, England Neeraj Yadav, Dancer in Bindass Naach and top 40 in So You Think You Can Dance(India).

The Department of Computer Science Presents.

2nd and 3 rd FEB

KC College:-   Kishinchand Chellaram College is one of the premier institutions affiliated to the University of Mumbai and recognized by Government of Maharashtra. It was established in 1954 by the Hyderabad (Sind) National Collegiate Board. The college was awarded permanent affiliation by the University of Mumbai within a record span of two years.

Over the years K.C. has established itself as one of the leading colleges in Mumbai. This fact is well supported by excellent results, both at HSC as well as at the University examinations and the number of laurels won by the students.

The Motto of the College is ‘SALVATION THROUGH KNOWLEDGE’. This motto was selected from ancient Sanskrit scriptures. ‘Knowledge’ in the highest sense means acquiring wisdom & understanding, which in turn leads man to ”Moksha” or Salvation.

K.C. prides itself in motivating students to achieve excellence not only in academic fields but also in co-curricular and extracurricular activities. With Ms. Manju Nichani as the Principal, the Signature Line of the College could well be – “Excellence - the only Compelling Option.”

TechClub:-  Fiestron – Our Tech Territory” is an initiative taken by the students of
the Department of Computer Science of K.C. College for their Annual
Festival.

Fies-Tron is an Inter collegiate fest of 2 days in which a lot of colleges
participate across Mumbai.

The aim of this festival is to introduce students to the recent developments
in the field of Computer Science in an exciting and interesting manner.

->Last year we had renowned personalities like:

->Mr. Keki Mistry, Vice Chairman and CEO of HDFC

->Robin Catchpole, astronomer at the Institute of Astronomy,
Cambridge, England

->Neeraj Yadav, Dancer in Bindass Naach and top 40 in So You

FIESTRON 2K18

"THE TECH TERRITORY"

REGISTER HERE "THE DEPARTMENT OF COMPUTER SCIENCE PRESENTS FIESTRON"

About Us

Our College


Kishinchand Chellaram College is one of the premier institutions affiliated to the University of Mumbai and recognized by Government of Maharashtra. It was established in 1954 by the Hyderabad (Sind) National Collegiate Board. The college was awarded permanent affiliation by the University of Mumbai within a record span of two years.

Our Fest


Fiestron – Our Tech Territory” is an initiative taken by the students of the Department of Computer Science of K.C. College for their Annual Festival. Fies-Tron is an Inter collegiate fest of 2 days in which a lot of colleges participate across Mumbai.The aim of this festival is to introduce students to the recent developments in the field of Computer Science in an exciting and interesting manner.

The Department of Computer Science

Department of Computer Science was started as Applied Component for B.Sc. and B.Com. in early 1980s. B.Sc. in Computer Science course was started in the year 1999, the same as the course was introduced by University of Mumbai. The department has always maintained a trend in securing top positions in the merit list of Mumbai University under Computer Science. Department not only sees the enhancement of the students by organizing various workshops and seminars for their overall development also motivate to actively participate in NSS and co-curricular activities. The department pledges with renewed verve, dynamism and zest to continue its pursuit towards brilliance in education for years to come.
